<br>
I encourage everyone to /feedback in game for them to find a better solution to this fix. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=velaelsoulrender>Velael Soulrender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>The Snuggly SZ'r!</span><br>  Posts: 1058<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/25/03 12:30:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26263.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: bow to bards</span><hr size=1> /shrug - there's a lot of people who thought Worry was a friend.<br>
<br>
He's a nice guy (girl? - he's never really said), with a strange sense of humor and style, both in-game and RL (have him show you pictures of his house and odds and ends collections ... it's wierd, to say the least). I don't have a problem with what he does, he certainly makes no bones about it or pretends it's something else. I've chatted with Worry quite a few times, mostly months ago on SZ. I don't dislike him, just I don't expect anything he does to be beneficial to anyone but him. If it helps someone else out, that's accidental but not all bad.<br>
<br>
But don't mistake it. EQ is a business for Worry, not a game. There's a very big difference, and forgetting that warps your perspective of the whole situation. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:courier;font-size:small;">&quot;It never stops hurting, you just go faster...&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> - <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:courier;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Greg LeMond</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyorg@graffeswizardcompilation>Gyorg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/25/03 1:35:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26263.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PBAE?</span><hr size=1> Are they leading the swarm of mobs around when they do this? If so it seems like the song they are using can't be a PBAE, since 'point blank' means the mobs are right next to you. Unless they have a larger radius than our PBAE nukes. Or unless they are standing still and twisting some kind of stun song. But it doesnt make sense that they would be able to nuke an unlimited number of mobs, from a distance, while running. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordbug>LordBug</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 680<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/25/03 1:39:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26263.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://lordbug.hypermart.net/icon3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PBAE?</span><hr size=1> He listed the songs he was using.  I know the first one (like level 2) is a PBAE.  I used to use it with my newbie bard a long time ago.  It does have quite a large range, but the damage is minimal.  I never considered doing something like what he's doing to PL a bard up.<br>
<br>
The better fix to HoH would've been either:<br>
A- Increase melee range of mobs<br>
B- Decrease area of these PBAE songs<br>
<br>
If Worry is the reason HoH got nerfed, they did it the wrong way. <p><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26448">Ebdain Ahriman</a><BR>
